external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" in this context refers to properties with a price per square meter above the average;
- "stand above the crowd" implies that the property prices are higher than the average price per square meter of all properties;
- "caught the eye of more than one curious visitor" means the property has been viewed more than once;
- "how much they sparkle per square meter" is a metaphor for the price per square meter.

- "sailors" refers to real estate agents;
- "vast ocean of real estate transactions" refers to the database containing numerous real estate transactions;
- "mettle" is used metaphorically to signify the ability and effectiveness of agents in handling transactions;
- "price waves" refers to the fluctuation in price per square meter of properties;
- "average height of those waves" is the average price per square meter of the properties they manage;
- "count of their voyages" refers to the number of transactions each agent has been involved in.

sql:
SELECT agency_name, address
FROM agencies
WHERE agency_id > 5;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT pv.property_id)
FROM property_views pv
JOIN reviews r ON pv.client_id = r.client_id AND pv.property_id = r.property_id;

SELECT agent_name
FROM agents
WHERE sales_performance = (SELECT MAX(sales_performance) FROM agents);

SELECT AVG(total_views) AS average_views
FROM (
    SELECT property_id, COUNT(view_id) AS total_views
    FROM property_views
    GROUP BY property_id
);

SELECT property_id, price_per_square_py
FROM properties
ORDER BY price_per_square_py DESC;
